  <h2>What Improved Under CPC</h2>
  <p>Prior to CPC's involvement in specific sites within the portfolio, common issues across Queensland Government cleaning contracts included: documentation that was assembled reactively in response to audit notices rather than maintained continuously; credential management processes that relied on self-declaration rather than verified records; and performance reporting that did not align with government format requirements, requiring manual conversion before submission.</p>
  <p>Under CPC's management, audit documentation is produced from continuously maintained operational records. WWCC and security credentials are managed through a central system with proactive renewal tracking. Performance reporting is generated in government-required formats as a standard output of the management system, not as a separate administrative task.</p>

  <h2>Lessons for Government Contracts</h2>
  <p>Continuation on a government panel is not automatic. It requires demonstrating consistent performance across audit cycles, maintaining certified management systems through annual surveillance, and producing evidence on demand without lead time. Providers who win government contracts without building the management infrastructure to sustain them consistently fail at the first major audit or panel review.</p>
  <p>The geographic range of a government portfolio is a stronger differentiator than most providers recognise. The ability to manage remote and regional sites is an operational capability that cannot be replicated through metropolitan expertise alone. For government portfolios spanning the full range of Queensland geography, this is often the capability gap that determines which providers remain on the panel through successive renewals.</p>

  <div class="cs-apply-box">
    <span class="cs-apply-box-label">How This Applies to Your Organisation</span>
    <p>If your government facility portfolio requires multi-site cleaning under a panel framework, the capability demonstrated in this case study is directly transferable. The management systems, credential frameworks and reporting infrastructure that sustain 252 Queensland Government sites apply equally to a single-agency portfolio or a multi-department contract. Active QBuild Panel position provides the most direct proxy for government cleaning compliance readiness available from any provider in the Australian market.</p>
    <p>For procurement teams evaluating tenders: ask every shortlisted provider to confirm current panel position on a state government cleaning panel, produce their ISO certificate numbers and expiry dates, and describe their credential management process for security-classified sites. These three questions will identify the compliance-ready providers without requiring an audit.</p>
